<p>I would really like to buy a new car but I&#8217;ve chosen not to because I don&#8217;t want to pay thousands of dollars to the state in sales tax.  If I got the ECM account with Oregon street address, would I be able to buy a car and register it in Oregon for a year, then &#8220;move&#8221; to my new state thus avoiding the sales tax of my state?  Maybe I would have to move &#8220;on paper&#8221;, including my Drivers license, title the car in Oregon and resister it in Oregon.  I have to wonder if it sets off a flag when someone tries to get a DL and uses the Oregon street address.  I mean, there can only reasonably be a limited number of people at that address.  Maybe there is a setup which could use apartment numbers or something so there are not 50 people trying to change their address to the same street address.</p>
